headline: NYC's office market comeback is 'unique' compared to other cities
summary: Office leasing activity in New York City surged by over 50% above the five-year average, according to commercial real estate group CBRE (CBRE), increasing to 8.36 million square feet in the third quarter. CBRE Group Vice Chairman John Maher speaks with Allie Canal on Market Catalysts about the state of the US commercial real estate market and why New York's comeback may be "unique" as compared to other major cities. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Catalysts.
